# Project-Specific Rules for Claude Code

## Git Commits
- Do NOT add "Generated with [Claude Code]" footer to commit messages
- Do NOT add "Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet" to commit messages
- Keep commit messages clean and follow the project's conventional commit style
- Commit messages should be concise and descriptive
- Commit should be in English
- NEVER automatically commit changes
- ONLY commit when explicitly requested by the user
- Do NOT ask the user if they want to commit after completing changes

## Git Push
- NEVER automatically push to main branch
- NEVER ask or suggest to push to main branch
- Only push when explicitly requested by the user for non-main branches
